   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Herakleides, son of Ammonios, farmer of the tax on catoecic registry for the Arsinoite and other nomes, to the recorder of the division of Herakleides, greeting. Gaius Apolinarius Niger, Antinoite, through Valerius Saturnilus, has registered the 5/8 aroura of confiscated(?) land, part of a catoecic allotment, which he acquired in Mecheir of the 16th year, formerly in the possession of Heron, son of Pekmeis, equals 5/8 aroura of grain land. Farewell. The 19th year of Aurelius Antoninus and Commodus, Caesars, our lords, Pauni 7.</ab>
         </div>
